“The new coat was conceptualised in an effort to promote road safety on this national route. We want to make drivers who pass the iconic rock conscious of the fact that they should act responsibly behind the wheel. Reckless and negligent driving is an ongoing problem and it is imperative that road users start obeying regulations for the safety of all. “Although the N4 Toll Route boasts world-class infrastructure, poor, negligent and disrespectful driving is a battle we keep fighting, because it puts everyone who uses our road at risk,” said Solange Soares, communications manager of TRAC N4. ALSO READ: First PUMA School of Speed in Mbombela